  {"a":"taric_sup","b":"zyra","win":["Zyra","Zyra","Zyra","Zyra","Zyra","Zyra","Taric"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 2","text":"Zyra spikes hard at 2 — a seeded Q plus E root and her plants melt your walk-ups, and with no gap-closer you eat the whole plant-empowered volley, so soak minimal poke behind minions and Q-heal it back."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Her R Stranglethorns is a delayed AoE knock-up that zones any all-in; your R Cosmic Radiance can cover your ADC through it, but you must have E-linked first — dive only when her E root is down."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Zyra's first AP item makes her plant poke and root brutal; you still can't close solo, so lean on your ADC's sustain and jungle pressure while you scale toward your Q-heal item spike."},{"when":"Late","text":"By two items your Bravado autos and W-stun engage let you E-close and lock her before she can seed plants, and your R negates her ultimate knock-up, flipping the timeline to Taric."}],"wants":{"you":["dodge her E root so her plants can't stack free damage on you","use minions as cover and Q-heal her plant poke between cooldowns","reach 2 items where W-stun engage closes before she seeds"],"foe":["seed Q and E then root you into a plant-empowered burst","zone your walk-ups with plants and out-poke your sustain","knock up your all-in with delayed R Stranglethorns"]},"early":"Zyra dominates 1-3: her seeded Q, E root and plants out-poke everything you have and you own no dash to punish her, so eat minimal harass, hide behind minions and heal the chip with Q charges.","mid":"Levels 4-6 stay hers — plant poke plus E root zones your approaches and her R adds a fight-ending knock-up, so only step up when her root is on cooldown and let your ADC farm safely.","late":"With two items your empowered autos, Q sustain and W stun let you E-link and lock her before she can seed, and Cosmic Radiance shrugs off her R — the reason the final phase colours Taric.","whys":["Zyra's plant-backed Q and E out-poke your dashless level-1 kit.","At 2 her seeded combo and plants chunk your walk-ups freely.","Level 3 adds full plant zoning and E root you can't answer.","Levels 4-5 she keeps kiting you with plants beyond your reach.","Her level-6 R knock-up zones your all-in from safe range.","First item deepens her poke lead before your sustain scales.","At 2+ items your W-stun engage and R invuln finally beat her plants."]}
